                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-8 col-lg-8 col-xl-8  res bg-light">
                    <div class="accordion  " id="accordion_general">
                       <div class="acordion_one" len="15243"><h3 len="22" lang="en"></h3> <div class="card" len="908"><div id="heading1_" class="card-header" len="279"><h2 class="mb-0" len="257"><button type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse1_" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse1_" class="btn btn-link collapsed" len="97" lang="en"> Declaration </button></h2></div> <div id="collapse1_" aria-labelledby="heading1_" data-parent="#accordion_general" class="collapse" len="477"><div class="card-body pl-4" len="443"><p len="436"><font lang="en"> This declaration is made in accordance with Law 985 of 2005 by means of which measures are adopted against modern slavery and trafficking in persons and international conventions such as the Palermo Protocol. </font><font lang="en">This statement sets out the steps Smirrow must take and constitutes our statement against slavery and human trafficking. </font></p></div></div></div> <div class="card" len="1105"><div id="heading1_1" class="card-header" len="278"><h2 class="mb-0" len="256"><button type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse1_1" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse1_1" class="btn btn-link collapsed" len="94" lang="en"> We </button></h2></div> <div id="collapse1_1" aria-labelledby="heading1_1" data-parent="#accordion_general" class="collapse" len="672"><div class="card-body pl-4" len="638"><p len="631"><font lang="en"> Smirrow is the platform that protects and revolutionizes the connection between users and service providers. </font><font lang="en">The site includes service providers and content creators of all genres and allows them to develop relationships based on freedom, security and trust with their users. </font><font lang="en">Smirrow provides service providers with the opportunity to monetize freely and independently and conducted in a secure environment that ensures full compliance with relevant laws, rules and regulations. </font></p></div></div></div> <div class="card" len="5015"><div id="heading1_2" class="card-header" len="279"><h2 class="mb-0" len="257"><button type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse1_2" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse1_2" class="btn btn-link collapsed" len="95" lang="en"> Policies </button></h2></div> <div id="collapse1_2" aria-labelledby="heading1_2" data-parent="#accordion_general" class="collapse" len="4581"><div class="card-body pl-4" len="4547"><p len="4540"><font><font lang="en"> Modern slavery and human trafficking is a crime and a violation of fundamental human rights. </font><font lang="en">It takes various forms such as slavery, servitude, forced and compulsory labour and trafficking in persons, all of which have in common the deprivation of liberty of one person by another for personal or commercial gain. </font><font lang="en">We have a zero-tolerance approach to modern slavery and human trafficking and are committed to acting ethically and whole in all our dealings and business relationships and, taking into account the structure of our sharing economy platform to implement and enforce effective systems to ensure that modern slavery and human trafficking is not being done. </font><font lang="en">That's why we don't allow people to be against their own will within the platform. </font></font><br len="0"><font><font lang="en"> We are committed to ensuring that no modern slavery or human trafficking activities take place on our platform or through our third-party suppliers. </font><font lang="en">Our Anti-Slavery and Human Trafficking Policy reflects our commitment to act ethically and with integrity in all of our business relationships and to implement and enforce effective systems and controls to ensure that slavery and human trafficking do not take place within the Smirrow community. </font></font><br len="0"><font><font lang="en"> The prevention, detection and reporting of modern slavery and human trafficking anywhere our sharing economy platform operates is the responsibility of all those who work for us, with us or under our control. </font><font lang="en">Our staff is obligated to avoid any activity that may lead to, or suggest, a breach of this statement. </font><font lang="en">All employees are required to read, understand, and fully comply with our Anti-Slavery and Human Trafficking Policy. </font><font lang="en">Internally, we inform and encourage our staff to report any concerns or irregularities that extend to any human rights violations such as modern slavery and human trafficking. </font><font lang="en">All reports will be thoroughly investigated and appropriate corrective action will be taken. </font><font lang="en">For our users, we have a community reporting process that allows anyone interested to report any violations of policies, regulations, and the law. </font><font lang="en">This can be done by contacting the seguridad@smirrow.com mail. </font></font><br len="0"><font><font lang="en"> We have whistleblowing policies that encourage our staff to report any concerns or irregularities that extend to human rights violations such as modern slavery and human trafficking. </font><font lang="en">All reports are investigated and appropriate action is taken. </font><font lang="en">If someone from the staff, user or third party presents a genuine concern, they will not suffer any harm as a result of doing so, even if it turns out to be wrong. </font></font><br len="0"><font><font lang="en"> We understand that our greatest exposure to modern slavery and human trafficking can occur within our platform. </font><font lang="en">We are committed to informing about the key points of action that we intend to carry out in the future for the safety and freedom of our users. </font></font><br len="0"><font lang="en"> The areas in which we operate could contain high-risk regions and we are aware of this. </font><br len="0"><font><font lang="en"> There are risks related to the provision of services and the risk that they will be used against your will by a third party and violate national rules, treaties, conventions and international protocols. </font><font lang="en">In order to disrupt and prevent harm, we monitor all media uploaded to the platform and remove, and report when necessary, any content that facilitates or coordinates the exploitation of humans, including human trafficking. </font><font lang="en">We define human trafficking as the business of depriving someone of liberty for profit. </font><font lang="en">It is exploitation of human beings to force them to engage in sexual, labor or other commercial activities against their will. </font><font lang="en">It is based on deceptive force or coercion. </font></font></p></div></div></div> <div class="card" len="1152"><div id="heading1_3" class="card-header" len="278"><h2 class="mb-0" len="256"><button type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse1_3" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse1_3" class="btn btn-link collapsed" len="94" lang="en"> Personnel </button></h2></div> <div id="collapse1_3" aria-labelledby="heading1_3" data-parent="#accordion_general" class="collapse" len="719"><div class="card-body pl-4" len="685"><p len="678"><font lang="en"> Our staff and suppliers regularly specify the Act as a contractual obligation that they must comply with and we will promote the requirement that any staff and supplier confirm their compliance with the Act. </font><font lang="en">That said, we have a limited number of staff and suppliers due to the nature of our industry. </font><font lang="en">We are implementing platform-wide training on modern slavery and human trafficking for all staff facing users and an annual review for everyone. </font><font lang="en">Training is mandatory. </font></p></div></div></div> <div class="card" len="896"><div id="heading1_4" class="card-header" len="285"><h2 class="mb-0" len="263"><button type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse1_4" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse1_4" class="btn btn-link collapsed" len="101" lang="en"> Risk areas </button></h2></div> <div id="collapse1_4" aria-labelledby="heading1_4" data-parent="#accordion_general" class="collapse" len="456"><div class="card-body pl-4" len="422"><p len="415"><font lang="en"> Safety. </font><font lang="en">We have a robust registration process when users join the platform to provide or request services. </font><font lang="en">This is a fundamental part of our zero-tolerance policies against modern slavery and human trafficking. </font><font lang="en">We have user verification methods for the account to be activated. </font></p></div></div></div> <div class="card" len="4474"><div id="heading1_5" class="card-header" len="293"><h2 class="mb-0" len="271"><button type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse1_5" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse1_5" class="btn btn-link collapsed" len="109" lang="en"> Content moderation </button></h2></div> <div id="collapse1_5" aria-labelledby="heading1_5" data-parent="#accordion_general" class="collapse" len="4026"><div class="card-body pl-4" len="3992"><p len="3985"><font><font lang="en"> We have developed the depth and sophistication of our content moderation where explicit nudity is not allowed. </font><font lang="en">This has included personal customer service onboarding to review content, in addition to our automated services. </font></font><br len="0"><font><font lang="en"> We monitor to make sure that only one user can create an account in their own name. </font><font lang="en">In addition, we apply this rule throughout your use of the platform. </font><font lang="en">We review any discrepancies between the added IDs and the legal name provided. </font></font><br len="0"><font><font lang="en"> We protect the identity of users, both those who provide services, and those who request services. </font><font lang="en">In no case does the platform expose personal data, nor their identities. </font></font><br len="0"><font><font lang="en"> We constantly make reports in order to significantly expand our support functions to address any concerns or complaints from our users and the community at large. </font><font lang="en">Our moderators internally review any reports derived from our platform. </font></font><br len="0"><font lang="en"> We will always be identifying and evaluating other areas of risk within our platform to improve the security and freedom of our users. </font><br len="0"><font lang="en"> Mitigate the risk of slavery and human trafficking that may occur on our platform. </font><br len="0"><font lang="en"> Protect whistleblowers within our platform and take appropriate corrective action as needed. </font><br len="0"><font><font lang="en"> As a user and part of the community you must keep up to date with recognized changes with respect to national legislation, conventions, treaties and related international protocols. </font><font lang="en">We are committed to the transparency of our platform and our approach to addressing modern slavery and human trafficking and any supply chain that is consistent with our obligations under national legislation, conventions, treaties and international protocols. </font><font lang="en">We expect very high standards within our platform and from our users, contractors, suppliers and our staff and include a specific prohibition against the use of force, forced or smuggling labour or any submission to slavery and human trafficking, whether adults or children. </font></font><br len="0"><font lang="en"> Monitor areas of potential risk and possible solutions to ensure that staff, users and any third parties are safe from the risk of slavery and human trafficking. </font><br len="0"><font lang="en"> We encourage anyone who finds content on Smirrow that indicates that someone is in immediate physical danger related to human trafficking to immediately report the content to us seguridad@smirrow.com. </font><br len="0"><font lang="en"> Responsibility for the declaration </font><br len="0"><font><font lang="en"> Our Executive Management has overall responsibility for ensuring that all those under our control comply with this statement and our related policies. </font><font lang="en">Management at all levels is responsible for ensuring that their teams understand this statement and comply with our Anti-Slavery and Anti-Trafficking Policy. </font><font lang="en">Smirrow's legal team has primary and day-to-day responsibility for dealing with this statement and any inquiries in this regard and considering internal control systems and procedures to ensure they are effective in the fight against modern slavery and human trafficking. </font></font></p></div></div></div> <div class="card" len="1422"><div id="heading1_6" class="card-header" len="282"><h2 class="mb-0" len="260"><button type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse1_6" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse1_6" class="btn btn-link collapsed" len="98" lang="en"> Compliance </button></h2></div> <div id="collapse1_6" aria-labelledby="heading1_6" data-parent="#accordion_general" class="collapse" len="985"><div class="card-body pl-4" len="951"><p len="944"><font lang="en"> Compliance with the risks faced by our platform due to modern slavery and human trafficking, is mandatory for all, includes our staff, users, contractors and suppliers, according to national legislation, treaties, conventions and international protocols, our staff will always be obliged to comply with them. </font><br len="0"><font lang="en"> Our approach against modern slavery and human trafficking will continue to be communicated across our platform and to any suppliers at the beginning of any business relationship with them and will be strengthened as appropriate thereafter. </font><br len="0"><font lang="en"> We are committed to maintaining and improving our practices to combat slavery and human trafficking. </font></p></div></div></div> <br len="0"> <br len="0"> <br len="0"> <br len="0"> <br len="0"> <br len="0"> <br len="0"> <br len="0"> <br len="0"> <br len="0"> <br len="0"> <br len="0"> <br len="0"></div>
